<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-259-017 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 631 711</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Seybold Report on Publishing Systems  Nov 12 1990 v20 n5p29(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Seybold Publications Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>OSF releases its merged Unix; New operating system to challengeATandamp;T's System 6? (the Open Software Foundation's OSF/1 operatingsystem) (The Latest Word) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Product:   OSF 1 (Operating system) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     UNIX-Like Operating SystemsCompatible SoftwareProduct IntroductionConsortiaOpen Software Foundation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>OSF releases its merged Unix The Open Software Foundation (OSF) hasintroduced the first commercial release of the OSF/1 operating system.andP;  Thisoperating system is the key component of the software architecture beingdeveloped jointly by a group of vendors opposed to leaving control of Unixwith ATandamp;T and Sun Microsystems.andM;But of the seven sponsoring OSF members, only DEC has promised to make OSF/1available across its full line of Unix workstations in 1991.andP;  IBM, HP, Bulland Hitachi said that they would gradually phase the new software into theirproduct lines over the next several years.andP;  Two members, Siemens and Philips,have not yet committed to using OSF/1 at all.andM;OSF/Motif, a graphical user interface that runs on top of OSF/1, and theDistributed Computing Environment, a set of software services with whichapplications may be written to share processing burdens across multiplecomputers, are the other key components at this time.andM;OSF/1 includes components from several OSF members.andP;  The kernel is based onMach, developed at Carnegie-Mellon University.andP;  &quot;Significant portions&quot; of theIBM AIX 3.1 operating system have been blended in, as have Encore Computer'ssymmetric multi-processing, SecureWare's SMP + security technology, Mentat'sStreams networking technology, the Berkeley 4.4 virtual file system andnetwork and local file systems from the University of California at Berkeley.andM;OSF/1's command set merges Unix System V and Berkeley 4.3 commands, providingcompatibility at the programming interface level with both versions of Unix.andO;It also complies with Posix and the X/Open Portability Guide.andP;  OSF/1 addsunique internationalization features.andM;OSF/1 is available now from OSF.andP;  The distribution tape includes theoperating system for the following platforms: Intel 80386, Digital DECstation3100 (based on the MIPS processor), Encore Multimax (based on NationalSemiconductor), HP DN2500, Intergraph 6000 and Intel 860.andM;OSF/Motif toolkits were introduced in 1989 and are now widely used byapplication developers.andP;  The distributed computing environment developer'skit is slated for release in early 1991.andM;The next technologies to be offered will be a vendor-neutral softwaredistribution format and the distributed management environment for managingheterogeneous networks.andO;</TEXT></DOC>